a - Anna (1851-1923) [wife of Vaclav Houdek from Mysliv, traveled with her son]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:2CSF-BNX|title=Maryland, Baltimore Passenger Lists, 1820-1948|last=Ticha|first=|date=1903|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nHoudek - Josef (1885-1962)\n|[[File:Anna Tichov\u00e1-Houdek (1851-1923).png|center|thumb|174x174px|Anna Tichov\u00e1-Houdek (1851-1923)]]\n|-\n|2 June 1903\n[[SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Grosse|SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Gro\u00dfe]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:SS Kaiser Wilhelm der Gro\u00dfe.png|center|thumb]]<br />\n|10 June 1903\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|Paty - Anezka (1882-1960) [to meet unknown A Havlik]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFRN-929|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Paty|first=|date=1903|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|12 January 1904\n[[SS Kaiser Wilhelm II]]\n\n[[Bremen]][[File:Kaiser wilhelm 2.jpg|center|thumb|172x172px]]\n|20 January 1904\n[[Ellis Island|New York]]\n|Protiva - Petr (1885-1973)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:JFB7-6NT|title=New York Passenger Arrival Lists (Ellis Island), 1892-1924|last=Protiva|first=|date=1904|website=FamilySearch|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nPetr was the younger brother of Marie.\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1904\n[[Baltimore]]\n|Houdek - Anna (1890-1963)\n|\n|-\n|\n|c. 1905\n|Stepan - Josefa (1894-1967)\n\nJosefa arrived with her adoptive family.\n|[[File:Josephine \u0160t\u011bp\u00e1nov\u00e1-Vlastnik-Krnak (1894-1967).png|center|thumb|141x141px|Josephine \u0160t\u011bp\u00e1nov\u00e1/Vlastnik-Krnak (1894-1967)]]\n|-\n|\n|c. 1905\n|Houdek - Anezka (1886-1960)\n\nAnezka was the daughter of Anna Tichova.\n|[[File:Agnes Houdkov\u00e1-Player (1886-1960).png|center|thumb|Agnes Houdkov\u00e1-Player (1886-1960)]]\n|-\n|24 April 1906\n\n[[SS Kron